<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="56" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1086,1579]" box="[151,635,1086,1111]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,635,1086,1111]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="Lepeletier 1833" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1833" box="[151,635,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rupestris" subSpecies="vasco">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,635,1086,1111]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,425,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Bombus rupestris vasco</emphasis>
(Lepeletier 1833)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1086,1579]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
This endemic subspecies spreads through the Pyrenees, the Cantabrian Range, Sierra de los Ancares, Sierra de Béjar, the Iberian system and the provinces of Logroño and Segovia, between 800 and 
<quantity box="[1131,1216,1159,1183]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
of altitude (
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" refString="Ornosa, C. &amp; Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J. (2004) Hymenoptera: Apoidea I. In: Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Fol. 23. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 556." type="book chapter" year="2004">Ornosa &amp; Ortiz-Sánchez 2004</bibRefCitation>
). It was common in the past in the Pyrenees (55 recorded individuals, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[1202,1349,1195,1219]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" refString="Ornosa, C. (1984) La subfamilia Bombinae (Hym., Apidae) de la fauna espanola. Coleccion Tesis Doctorales, n ° 203 / 84, Ed. Universidad Complutense de Madrid, Madrid, 334 pp." type="book" year="1984">Ornosa 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[1361,1432,1194,1219]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" refString="Ornosa, C. (1986 a) Especies de Bombinae de la Sierra de los Ancares (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Actas de las FIII Jornadas de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia, Sevilla, 1986, 1042 - 1050." type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="a">1986a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[151,421,1230,1255]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" refString="Ornosa, C. &amp; Gayubo, S. F. (1989) Notas sobre los Bombinae de la Sierra de Bejar (Hym., Apidae). Boletin de la Asociacion espanola de Entomologia, 13, 173 - 182." type="journal article" year="1989">Ornosa &amp; Gayubo 1989</bibRefCitation>
, Castro 1989).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1086,1579]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
Currently, it is rare (
<tableCitation box="[423,508,1266,1291]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1394,332,1883]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Bumblebee species and subspecies collected in the Pyrenees and IUCN category ranks (from Spain: Verdú &amp; Galante (2006), Verdú et al. (2011) and from Europe: Rasmont et al. (2015): Not Evaluated, NE; Endangered, EN; Vulnerable, VU; Data Deficient, DD; Least Concern, LC) of the extant bumblebee species and subspecies in the Pyrenees. The number of individuals sampled between 2006 and 2015 is indicated. In rare species and those with relevant records, the number of individuals known from historical literature or collections is included in brackets." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" tableUuid="BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5">Table 2</tableCitation>
) and has been collected only three times in supraforestal grassland, with patches of subalpine scrubland, between 
<date box="[494,664,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" value="1589" valueMax="1882">
1589 and 
<quantity box="[608,664,1303,1327]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.882" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="1882.0">1882</quantity>
</date>
m (
<figureCitation box="[712,781,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) 
<collectedFrom box="[798,1150,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
on 
<taxonomicName authority="Gouan." authorityName="Gouan." box="[834,1150,1302,1327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Eryngium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bourgatii">
<emphasis box="[834,1057,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Eryngium bourgatii</emphasis>
Gouan.
</taxonomicName>
</collectedFrom>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1332,1302,1327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Gentiana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis box="[1163,1332,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Gentiana lutea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lotus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corniculatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Lotus corniculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[344,570,1338,1363]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Medicago" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis box="[344,534,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Medicago sativa</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. There" authorityName="L. There" box="[638,961,1338,1363]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratense">
<emphasis box="[638,850,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Trifolium pratense</emphasis>
L. There
</taxonomicName>
is another recent record from Sierra del Caurel in Galicia (Lugo: Liñares, 
<quantity box="[530,617,1375,1399]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="1300.0">1300 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[629,721,1375,1399]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" value="2010-09-03">3-IX-10</date>
, 1 male, R. Outerelo leg., UCME).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1086,1579]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
According to current records, 
<taxonomicName box="[556,684,1412,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rupestris" subSpecies="vasco">
<emphasis box="[556,684,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">B. r. vasco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is decreasing in the Pyrenees (
<tableCitation box="[1060,1150,1410,1435]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1394,332,1883]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Bumblebee species and subspecies collected in the Pyrenees and IUCN category ranks (from Spain: Verdú &amp; Galante (2006), Verdú et al. (2011) and from Europe: Rasmont et al. (2015): Not Evaluated, NE; Endangered, EN; Vulnerable, VU; Data Deficient, DD; Least Concern, LC) of the extant bumblebee species and subspecies in the Pyrenees. The number of individuals sampled between 2006 and 2015 is indicated. In rare species and those with relevant records, the number of individuals known from historical literature or collections is included in brackets." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" tableUuid="BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5">Table 2</tableCitation>
) and it shows a greater elevational tendency in the lower level of its range (
<figureCitation box="[732,801,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
